dcterms:description: A modified version of the IEEE 33-bus system used to analyze the impact of different EV charging levels on the power quality of the electricity distribution network.
dcterms:title: IEEE 33-bus system

dcterms:description: Normalized hourly demand data from California ISO used to set the base net demand and solar generation trends for the analysis.
dcterms:title: California ISO normalized hourly demand

dcterms:description: Data on solar generation units used to analyze their impact on the voltage profile of the distribution network.
dcterms:title: Solar generation units

dcterms:description: Various scenarios of EV charging levels (fast charging, combined, level 2 charging) analyzed for their impact on the distribution network.
dcterms:title: EV charging scenarios (fast charging, combined, level 2 charging)

dcterms:description: Scenarios related to the cost of battery degradation for EVs, analyzed for their impact on the operation of the distribution network.
dcterms:title: Battery degradation cost scenarios
